  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Support for Drought affected Households in Isiolo County</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a project to improve the lives of vulnerable people in Isiolo County who have been devastated by recent severe drought.  Prolonged drought in Kenya has resulted in water and pasture shortages and food insecurity situation. The crisis was exacerbated by the failure of the October-December 2016 short rains.  In February 2017, the Government of Kenya declared the drought a national disaster and appealed for international support to save the lives of vulnerable people threatened by drought. 
CAFOD through DEC and CAFOD appeal is planning to work with Caritas Isiolo to address issues of water shortage, food insecurity, health and nutrition needs, livestock feeds, and convene peace meetings in critical locations.  CAFOD and partners will work through existing humanitarian forums both at national and the County levels to maximise available support.</narrative>
  </description>
